docker compose start grafana

# Repeat for Loki:
docker compose stop loki
sudo tar -czf /opt/backups/loki-$(date +%Y%m%d).tar.gz /var/lib/docker/volumes/loki-data/_data/
docker compose start loki

Ansible Playbooks:
ssh jireland@mgmt.lab.local
tar -czf /opt/backups/ansible-$(date +%Y%m%d).tar.gz /opt/ansible/

==== Backup Verification ====

Daily Verification (Automated):

Check backup files exist:
ssh [user]@apps.lab.local
ls -lh /opt/backups/

Check file sizes (should be non-zero):
du -sh /opt/backups/*
# All files should show reasonable sizes

Check latest backup timestamp:
ls -lt /opt/backups/ | head
# Should show recent files (within 24 hours)

Check Ansible Playbook Output:

After running backup-homelab.yml:
- All tasks should show 'ok' or 'changed'
- No tasks should show 'failed'
- Review PLAY RECAP for any failures

Monthly Restore Test (1st of Month):

Procedure:

1. Select random service backup:
ls /opt/backups/gitea-*.tar.gz | shuf -n 1

2. Create test restore location:
mkdir -p /tmp/restore-test

3. Extract backup:
tar -xzf /opt/backups/[selected-backup].tar.gz -C /tmp/restore-test

4. Verify data integrity:
ls -R /tmp/restore-test
# Check files exist and sizes are reasonable

5. For database backups, verify SQL is valid:
head -50 /opt/backups/gitea-db-[date].sql
# Should show valid SQL statements

6. Document test results:
echo “$(date): Tested [backup-file] - SUCCESS” » /opt/ansible/logs/restore-tests.log

7. Clean up:
rm -rf /tmp/restore-test

