==== Restore Procedures ====

Restore PostgreSQL Database (Gitea):

ssh [user]@apps.lab.local

# Stop Gitea to prevent writes:
docker compose stop gitea

# Drop existing database (CAREFUL!):
docker exec -it postgres psql -U gitea -c “DROP DATABASE gitea;”
docker exec -it postgres psql -U gitea -c “CREATE DATABASE gitea;”

# Restore from backup:
docker exec -i postgres psql -U gitea gitea < /opt/backups/gitea-db-YYYYMMDD.sql

# Start Gitea:
docker compose up -d gitea

# Verify:
docker logs gitea
# Check for successful startup, no database errors

Restore MariaDB Database (WordPress):

ssh jireland@apps.lab.local

# Stop WordPress:
docker compose stop wordpress

# Restore database:
docker exec -i mariadb mysql -u root -pPASSWORD wordpress < /opt/backups/wordpress-db-YYYYMMDD.sql

# Start WordPress:
docker compose up -d wordpress

# Verify:
curl http://blog.lab.local
# Should load WordPress site

Restore Service Data (Bind Mounts):

Example: Restore Gitea files

ssh [user]@apps.lab.local

# Stop service:
docker compose stop gitea

# Backup current data (just in case):
mv /opt/docker/gitea /opt/docker/gitea.old

# Extract backup:
tar -xzf /opt/backups/gitea-YYYYMMDD.tar.gz -C /
# Note: This restores to original path /opt/docker/gitea

# Fix permissions if needed:
sudo chown -R jireland:jireland /opt/docker/gitea

# Start service:
docker compose up -d gitea

# Verify:
docker logs gitea
# Check service starts successfully

# Clean up old backup if successful:
rm -rf /opt/docker/gitea.old

Restore Docker Volumes (mntr.lab.local):

