==== Best Practices ====

Backup Practices:

- Always verify backups completed (check file sizes)
- Test restore monthly (1st of each month)
- Keep backups for at least 7 days
- Encrypt backups before offsite storage
- Document restore procedures for each service
- Monitor disk space in /opt/backups

Restore Practices:

- Always backup current state before restoring
- Test restore in non-production environment first (if possible)
- Verify data integrity after restore
- Check service logs after restore
- Document restore process and results

Security Practices:

- Restrict backup directory permissions (chmod 700)
- Encrypt offsite backups (GPG)
- Store encryption keys securely (not with backups)
- Rotate backup encryption keys annually
- Audit backup access logs

Operational Practices:

- Review backup logs weekly
- Clean old backups automatically (7-day retention)
- Update documentation after any changes
- Test disaster recovery scenarios quarterly
- Keep backup procedures simple and documented

