Vaultwarden Database:

Location: Docker volume on apps.lab.local

Backed Up: Nightly (included in Docker volume backups)

Contains: All password entries, folders, secure notes

Restoration:

```bash # Restore Docker volumes from backup docker compose down sudo tar -xzf backup.tar.gz -C /opt/docker/ docker compose up -d vaultwarden

# Verify Vaultwarden accessible curl -I https://vault.lab.local ```

Ansible Vault:

Location: `/opt/ansible/vars/vault.yml` on mgmt.lab.local

Backed Up: - Version controlled in git (encrypted state) - Nightly backups of /opt/ansible/ directory

Contains: All infrastructure passwords and secrets (encrypted)

Restoration:

```bash # Option 1: Restore from git history cd /opt/ansible git log vars/vault.yml git checkout COMMIT_HASH – vars/vault.yml

# Option 2: Restore from backup sudo cp backup/vault.yml /opt/ansible/vars/vault.yml

# Verify vault decrypts ansible-vault view /opt/ansible/vars/vault.yml ```

Critical Offline Backups:

Store in secure offline location: - Vaultwarden master password (written down, safe location) - Ansible vault password (also in Vaultwarden, but backup offline) - SSH private key passphrases (if used)

Without these, recovery is impossible if Vaultwarden is lost.

